Updated all configuration examples and documentation in `TfsNodeStructureTool-notes.md` from the legacy format to the new structured format developed by @satano.

## Changes Made

**Configuration Format Migration:**
- `NodeBasePaths` ‚Üí `Areas.Filters` and `Iterations.Filters`
- `AreaMaps` ‚Üí `Areas.Mappings` with structured `Match`/`Replacement` objects
- `IterationMaps` ‚Üí `Iterations.Mappings` with structured `Match`/`Replacement` objects

**Old Format:**
```json
{
  "$type": "TfsNodeStructureOptions",
  "NodeBasePaths": ["*\\Team 2", "*\\Sprint*"],
  "AreaMaps": {
    "^OriginalProject\\\\(DescopeThis|DescopeThat)": "TargetProject\\Archive\\Descoped\\"
  },
  "IterationMaps": {
    "^OriginalProject\\\\Path1(?=\\\\Sprint 2022)": "TargetProject\\AnotherPath\\NewTeam"
  }
}
```

**New Format:**
```json
{
  "Areas": {
    "Filters": ["*\\Team 2"],
    "Mappings": [
      {
        "Match": "^OriginalProject\\\\(DescopeThis|DescopeThat)(.*)$",
        "Replacement": "TargetProject\\Archive\\Descoped\\$1$2"
      }
    ]
  },
  "Iterations": {
    "Filters": ["*\\Sprint*"],
    "Mappings": [
      {
        "Match": "^OriginalProject\\\\Path1(?=\\\\Sprint 2022)(.*)$",
        "Replacement": "TargetProject\\AnotherPath\\NewTeam$1"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

## Documentation Updates

- ‚úÖ Updated all JSON configuration examples throughout the document
- ‚úÖ Updated Filters section table to use new property structure
- ‚úÖ Updated explanatory text and bullet points to reference new format
- ‚úÖ Updated warning text to reflect `Match`/`Replacement` property structure
- ‚úÖ Converted all examples from key-value mapping pairs to structured objects
- ‚úÖ Fixed terminology references throughout the document
- ‚úÖ Verified changes by running documentation generator successfully

The documentation now consistently uses the new format across all examples, making it easier for users to configure TfsNodeStructureTool with the current implementation.

